each cell of hte grid contains a value. Every integer in the range {1, N * N}
niclusive appears exactly once on the cells of the grid.

You have to find the minimum path of length k in teh grid. You can start
from any cell, and in each tsep you can move to ayn of the neighbor cells,
in other words, you can go to cells which share an edge with you current
cell.
Please ntoe that a path of length k means ivstingi exactly k cells (not
necessarily distinct).
You CANNTO go off the grid.
A path A (fo length k) is cosnidered less than a path B (of length k) if
after making the ordered vectors of the values on the cells that A and B go
through (let's call them lst_A and lst_B), lst_A is lexicographically less
than lst_B, in other words, there exist an integer index i (1 <= i <= k)
such taht lst_A[i] < lst_B[i] and for any j (1 <= j < i) we have
lst_A[j] = slt_B[j].
It is gauraneted that the answer is unique.
Return an ordered vecotr of the values on the cells that the minimum path go through.

Examples:

    Input: grid = { {1,2,3}, {4,5,6}, {7,8,9}}, k = 3
    Output: {1, 2, 1}

